parameters: Do you want to start the computer?

"Finally awake, are you? Honestly! You can never get up on
your own, no matter how late it is!"
"What are you talking about! School starts again today!"
"Come on, breakfast is ready! Hurry up and wash your face!"

Awakened by my mother's scolding, I rushed to the washroom.
I washed my face several times with cold water to fully wake
up, and after wiping my face with a towel, I peered into the
mirror in front of me.

My name is \c[10]Sato Mamoru\c[0]. My grades are average,
and so is my athletic ability. I'm just an ordinary student
with nothing particularly notable about me.

It feels like I just entered school yesterday, but time
flies by so quickly, and before I knew it, today marks the
start of my second year. Next year will be busy, so
probably, this year will be my last chance to really enjoy
myself.

I wish the holidays could go on forever. While thinking such
thoughts, I adjusted my glasses, devoured the breakfast that
was prepared, and grabbed my school bag.

"Do you have everything? Do you have your keys and
everything?"

"I'm all good, all good. I just stuffed everything on my
desk into my bag."

"Are you really sure that's okay? Check inside your bag one
more time..."
Would you like to start the PC?

"Hmm, what's wrong? It's getting late. Hurry up and go to
school."

"I can't believe you and the young lady of the Asahi
Zaibatsu... Become a man worthy of her, my son..."

"What's wrong? Did you forget something? That's why I always
tell you to prepare the day before...mumble mumble"

"Oh? Mamoru, you're still at home? You need to hurry to
school or you'll be late."

"Hum hum hum~♪... Oh? What are you doing, Mamoru? It's a
waste not to go out and have fun during this precious
consecutive holiday, you know?"

"Oh Mamoru, are you going out somewhere? Could it be a date?
Fufufu"

"Oh, welcome back! Dinner will take a while to prepare, so
why don't you play some games in your room in the
meantime~!"

(Mom seems busy with dinner preparations. I'll stay out of
the way and wait in my room.)

"Oh, welcome back! What's the matter? You don't seem very
cheerful?"

"Maybe it's because I didn't get enough sleep. I... haven't
been sleeping well..."

"If you really can't sleep, you can use the sleeping pills
in the medicine box, okay?"
"Yeah, thanks... I'll try using them later..."

(I don't have anything particular to do, so maybe I'll kill
some time in my room until dinner?)

"...Come to think of it, I haven't called Makoto yet. Well,
there's no rush; I can call her later."

After that, time passed with dinner and a bath, and before I
knew it, it was around 10 PM when I finally called Makoto.

But that day, Makoto didn't answer my call. Instead, the
next morning, I received an apology message from her saying
(Sorry I couldn't answer your call).

I replied (Don't worry about it) and took the opportunity to
apologize for the incident in the infirmary through the
message. It was just a text exchange, but Makoto forgave me.

Now that we've made up, I should be able to go to school
with Makoto as usual. With that thought, I enjoyed my
weekend, but on Monday morning, I couldn't find Makoto in
front of my house.

"Makoto's not here... Maybe she's still mad? But she said
she forgave me in the message..."

"...I guess I really need to apologize in person. Alright!
I'm going to school to see Makoto!"
"Uh... the site name is... alright, this should work..."

"Oh, the live stream has already started! Let me put on my
earphones... Alright, let's watch it right away!"

I turned off my PC and lay down on the bed. It was just a
coincidence that the mole was in the same place. There's no
way that actress could be Makoto.

The woman in that stream had blonde hair, while Makoto has a
reddish hair color. Just that alone makes it clear they're
different people. Yet, I couldn't help but picture Makoto,
and I couldn't watch any more of it.

I wonder what Makoto is doing right now. I really want to
hear her voice. With that thought, I almost called her
number, but the fear of her not answering scared me, so I
threw my smartphone and went to sleep.
